# Theme Token Enforcement

The app has a theme configuration at `@/shared/constants/theme`. Every color, background, border, shadow, and surface value in a component must use a token from that object. Never write hardcoded color literals.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
background: "rgba(0,0,0,0.35)"
border: "1px solid #C9A770"
color: "white"

// ✅ GOOD
import { theme } from "@/shared/constants/theme";
background: theme.cardHoverBarBg
border: `1px solid ${theme.borderStrong}`
color: theme.fg
```

Before adding any color value to a component, check what tokens are available in the theme file and use the closest match. If no token fits, ask whether a new token should be added to the theme rather than hardcoding.
